/*
:name: underflow_unsigned
:type: error
:error: does not fit
*/

// Underflow: a value/range that dips below an unsigned type's minimum (here a
// negative value into u4) does not fit. The escape is an explicit wrap/sat or a
// cast. Doc/decision (2026-05-31): all negatives into unsigned are an error,
// judged on the actual inferred range (so `u4 = a-b` is fine when the range is
// provably non-negative).

const c:u4 = -1
